ck product labels and test products out on a small patch of skin before applying to the face. This can aid in making choices that are less likely to aggravate Fungal Acne.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>When it comes to ingredients that can worsen Fungal Acne, there are a few to watch out for:&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1690789361483" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1690789361483"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>Fatty Acids and Oils:</strong></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1690789538394" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1690789538394"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-family: Poppins; color: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Yeast loves to feast on fatty acids and oils, so using skincare products that contain these can fuel the growth and spread of Fungal Acne. Look out for ingredients like:</span><br></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1688650268674" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1688650268674" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1688647242515" data-id="1688647242515"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1688650268577" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1688650268577"><div class="elm text-edit gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-